name: Dubai flooding
summary: Unprecedented heavy rains have caused havoc across the Middle East, particularly in Dubai and Oman. The torrential downpours have led to widespread flooding, disrupting flights at Dubai Airport, where operations were halted due to water damage. Buildings have been damaged, and the death toll in Oman has risen to 18. The rainfall in Dubai was equivalent to two years' worth of rain in just 24 hours, causing extensive flooding and chaos. Despite speculation, it has been confirmed that cloud seeding was not the cause of the heavy rainfall. The flooding has raised concerns about infrastructure and preparedness for extreme weather events in the region.

name: U.K smoking ban
summary: The United Kingdom has taken a groundbreaking step towards reducing smoking-related health issues by passing a bill in the House of Commons to prohibit the sale of cigarettes to anyone born after 2009. The bill, known as Rishi Sunak's anti-smoking bill, aims to create a "smoke-free generation" by preventing future generations from starting to smoke. The bill has received support from health experts and organizations but has also faced opposition from some Conservative MPs who believe it is an infringement on personal liberty. Despite the controversy, the bill has passed its first parliamentary hurdle and is expected to become law in the coming months. If implemented, it will be the most stringent smoking ban in the world and could potentially save thousands of lives in the long term.

summary: Blake Griffin, a six-time NBA All-Star and former Rookie of the Year, has announced his retirement after 13 seasons in the NBA. Despite his challenges, Griffin is grateful for his time in the NBA and expressed his appreciation for the experiences he's had. His retirement has sparked discussions about his potential Hall of Fame induction, with many believing his exceptional talent and accomplishments deserve recognition.

name: Big Mac Chant
summary: McDonald's has revived its iconic Big Mac Chant challenge, partnering with Snapchat, DDB, and OMD. Customers can now participate by saying 15 specific words at a McDonald's counter within four seconds, potentially winning free food. The challenge encourages Aussies to "untwist their tongues" for a chance to win free fries and Coke. McDonald's aims to "pass the baton of the chant between generations," reviving the 1987 promotion with a modern twist. The challenge has been extended as part of the "The Original Mouthful" campaign, giving customers a chance to win freebies by mastering the iconic Big Mac jingle.
